did.unittitle: Wine Institute Records on the American Wine Industry
did.abstract: The Wine Institute Records on the American Wine Industry includes winery survey data, county records, and regional growing histories; wine lists and menus; wine labels; speeches by wine scholars, producers and writers; promotional materials; materials related to wine and popular culture; photographs; film and video; and a small amount of microfilm containing biographies of wine industry leaders, winery information, historical data, and surveys.
did.physloc: Researchers should contact Archives and Special Collections to request collections, as many are stored offsite.

bioghist.head: History
bioghist.p: The Wine Institute was established in 1934 to serve as a lobbying, promotional, and educational organization for the wine industry. Membership consists of California grape growers and wine makers.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The collection includes winery survey data, county records, and regional growing histories; wine lists and menus; wine labels; speeches by wine scholars, producers and writers; promotional materials; materials related to wine and popular culture; photographs; film and video; and a small amount of microfilm containing biographies of wine industry leaders, winery information, historical data, and surveys.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is not yet fully processed. Please contact Special Collections in advance to request access.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: This collection is being processed by Liz Phillips with the help of cataloger Steffany Caria and student assistants Kelsey Haydon, Husnain Jafrani, and Aditi Sinha.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [Identification of item], Wine Institute Records on the American Wine Industry, D-242, Archives and Special Collections, UC Davis Library, University of California, Davis.

userestrict.head: Publication Rights
userestrict.p: All applicable copyrights for the collection are protected under chapter 17 of the U.S. Copyright Code. Requests for permission to publish or quote from manuscripts must be submitted in writing to the Head of Special Collections. Permission for publication is given on behalf of the Regents of the University of California as the owner of the physical items. It is not intended to include or imply permission of the copyright holder, which must also be obtained by the researcher.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Wine Institute reference and working files, including reports, publicity, subject files, and publications. Arranged by Wine Institute subject classification when possible.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Biographies of wine industry leaders, winery information, historical data, and surveys. This information is likely duplicated in print.

did.unittitle: California Wine and Food Center in New York - Proposals, correspondence, surveys, events

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Proposals: "A Proposal For A National Wine Education Program: A Comprehensive Consumer and Trade Effort On Behalf of the Winegrowers of California" by The Wine Institute ; "A Proposal For the Development of the California Wine and Food Center In New York City" submitted by The Wine Institute. Correspondence between the Wine Institute and various California fruit and vegetable advisory boards regarding their interest in participating in the proposed California Food and Wine Center in New York City (most were interested in the concept but not interested in assisting in financing it). Written questionnaire responses from various California fruit and vegetable advisory boards returned to the Wine Institute regarding marketing for their respective products, details about their products and organizations, and interest in marketing their products in New York. Event information concerning several Wine Institute events held in New York City.

did.unittitle: Montana - Newspaper and political advertisement clippings and correspondence regarding Montana Initiative 81 - The Table Wine Bill - allowing a free market distribution of table wines in the State of Montana.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Newspaper and political advertisement clippings and correspondence regarding Montana Initiative 81 - The Table Wine Bill - which would allow a free market distribution of table wines in the State of Montana (it passed in December 1978). Includes Wine Institute correspondence with the leader of the organization that authored the Initiative, Leonard Eckel of Montanans Who Like Wine P.A.C., as well as political ad clippings from the PAC and opponents of the Initiative and correspondence with the State of Montana.

did.unittitle: New York - The Association of American Vintners - Correspondence concerning effort to assist in the networking among Northeast wine states on developing reciprocal interstate shipping legislation.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Correspondence from the Association of American Vinters based in New York to the Commissioner of the Connecticut Department of Agriculture concerning its efforts to assist in the networking among Northeast wine states on developing reciprocal interstate shipping legislation. They mention the recently passed state bill in California that permits out of state wineries to ship limited amounts of wine to legal age residents of California if the state from which the shipment is made similarly permits its residents to receive wine from California wineries. It also mentions the Wine Institute of California, which was the sponsor of the California bill, and that representatives of the Wine Institute of California would be willing to discuss their implementation methods and answer questions.
